Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a visual localization algorithm that uses multiple image descriptors to achieve accurate localization of key positions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision sub-category.
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper mentions a wearable system and testing the performance of visual localization under practical scenarios, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics sub-category.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper focuses on improving the navigational assistance for visually impaired people, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction sub-category.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper may also belong to the machine learning sub-category as it proposes a robust and efficient visual localization algorithm that takes advantage of priori GNSS signals and multi-modal images.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper uses multiple image descriptors to achieve accurate localization, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia sub-category.
